    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-10-23T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-10-23T08:00:00-05:00" n="486"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d486">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/3542: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Gibraltar</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Williams</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibraltar</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-10-23T13:00:00+00:00"
                            >October 23, 1936—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 23—10:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Italian ship <hi rend="italic">Esquilino</hi> arrived today at an early hour from
                    Naples landing 23 veterans of the Ethiopian campaign en route to Tangier and
                    Casablanca and 82 Spanish who are en route to Seville to join Franco’s
                    forces.</p>
                <p>Moorish troops continue to cross the Straits into Spain escorted by insurgent
                    warship.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Williams</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
